## Agent Compatibility Matrix

Here is exactly how DSAEngine integrates with each of the 7 supported agents — researched and verified:

### Tier 1 — Full Native MCP Stdio (Plug-and-play)

These agents run your binary directly as a child process via stdio. Zero HTTP, zero hosting.

| Agent | MCP Config File | Rules File | MCP Transport |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Claude Code** | `~/.claude/claude_desktop_config.json` | `CLAUDE.md` (project root) | stdio |
| **Cursor** | Settings → MCP tab (GUI) or `~/.cursor/mcp.json` | `.cursorrules` | stdio or HTTP |
| **Windsurf** | `~/.windsurf/mcp_config.json` | `.windsurfrules` | stdio, HTTP, SSE |
| **Kiro** (AWS) | `.vscode/mcp.json` or User Profile `mcp.json` | `.kiro/steering/*.md` | stdio |
| **GitHub Copilot** | VS Code `settings.json` → `github.copilot.mcp` | `.github/copilot-instructions.md` | stdio |
| **Augment Code** | Augment settings panel ("Easy MCP") | `augment-guidelines.md` | stdio/HTTP |
| **Google Antigravity** | Agent Manager UI → MCP Servers | `.agent/rules/*.md` or `CLAUDE.md` | stdio/HTTP |

**Stdio MCP config snippet (same format for all Tier 1 agents):**
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "dsaengine": {
      "command": "dsaengine",
      "args": ["--mcp"],
      "description": "DSAEngine — optimal algorithm advisor for vibe coders"
    }
  }
}
```

### Rules File Generation — All 7 Targets

