## Proposed Changes

### Component 1: MCP Stdio Server

#### [MODIFY] [main.rs](file:///c:/dsaengine/src/main.rs)
Add CLI flag detection. If `--mcp` is passed, run stdio mode instead of web server:

```rust
#[tokio::main]
async fn main() {
    let args: Vec<String> = std::env::args().collect();
    
    if args.contains(&"--mcp".to_string()) {
        // MCP stdio mode — zero cost, local, no HTTP
        mcp_stdio::run().await;
    } else {
        // Existing web server mode (for Render deployment)
        web_server::run_server().await;
    }
}
```

#### [NEW] [mcp_stdio.rs](file:///c:/dsaengine/src/mcp_stdio.rs)
The core stdio server. Reads JSON-RPC from stdin, writes to stdout:

```rust
// Reads stdin line by line (MCP uses newline-delimited JSON)
// Routes to the same handlers the web server uses
// Adds two new meta-tools: dsa_classify and dsa_suggest
// Zero network, zero API cost
```

Key functions:
- `run()` — Main stdin/stdout read loop
- `handle_initialize()` — Returns server capabilities
- `handle_tools_list()` — Lists all 142+ tools + classify + suggest
- `handle_tools_call()` — Dispatches to the right algorithm handler
