### Component 2: Deterministic DSA Classifier (No AI Needed)

#### [NEW] [src/utils/classifier.rs](file:///c:/dsaengine/src/utils/classifier.rs)
A keyword-based pattern matcher that recommends algorithms. **No AI API calls** — pure Rust string matching:

```rust
pub struct Recommendation {
    pub algorithm: &'static str,
    pub category: &'static str,
    pub confidence: f32,       // 0.0 - 1.0
    pub reason: &'static str,
    pub time_complexity: &'static str,
    pub space_complexity: &'static str,
    pub tool_name: &'static str,  // MCP tool to call
}

/// Classifies a problem description into algorithm recommendations.
/// Uses deterministic keyword/pattern matching — ZERO AI cost.
pub fn classify(description: &str) -> Vec<Recommendation> { ... }
```

**Pattern rules include:**

| Keywords Detected | Algorithm Recommended | Complexity |
|---|---|---|
| "shortest path" + "weighted" | Dijkstra | O(E log V) |
| "shortest path" + "negative" | Bellman-Ford | O(V·E) |
| "connected components" | Union-Find | O(α(n)) |
| "cache" + "eviction" | LRU/LFU Cache | O(1) |
| "substring" + "pattern" | KMP / Rabin-Karp | O(n+m) |
| "sorted array" + "search" | Binary Search | O(log n) |
| "minimum spanning" | Kruskal / Prim | O(E log V) |
| "topological" / "dependency order" | Topological Sort | O(V+E) |
| "sliding window" / "subarray sum" | Sliding Window | O(n) |
| "duplicate" / "frequency" | HashMap Counter | O(n) |
| "balanced tree" / "ordered set" | AVL Tree | O(log n) |
| "prefix" / "autocomplete" | Trie | O(L) |
| nested loop detected in code | Suggests HashMap/Set | O(n) → O(1) |

~100+ rules covering all 142 algorithms.

