## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Decision: Keep HTTP mode or go stdio-only?**
> 
> The current Render deployment (HTTP mode) serves a different purpose than the local MCP stdio mode. I recommend keeping BOTH:
> - `dsaengine` → HTTP web server (for Render, Swagger UI, direct API)
> - `dsaengine --mcp` → Local stdio server (for Cursor/Windsurf, zero cost)
> - `dsaengine --install` → Setup helper (generates rules files + config)

> [!WARNING]
> **The classifier rules need your domain expertise.**
> I'll implement ~100 keyword rules covering all 142 algorithms, but you should review the mappings since you know which algorithms map to which real-world problems best.

## Open Questions

1. **Distribution format**: Should users install via `cargo install dsaengine` (requires Rust toolchain) or download pre-built binaries from GitHub Releases? Or both?

2. **Algorithm output format**: When the LLM calls an algorithm tool, should it return:
   - (a) Just the **result** (e.g., shortest path = [1, 3, 5], cost = 12)
   - (b) The **Rust source code** of the algorithm for the LLM to adapt
   - (c) A **language-agnostic pseudocode** the LLM can translate to any language
   - (d) All of the above based on a `mode` parameter

3. **How many algorithms should `dsa_classify` recommend?** Top 1? Top 3 with confidence scores?

